Program: Omnibus
Title: The Space Telescope
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jtt
Last Broadcast Date: 17 April 1990
Looking forward to the launch of the Hubble telescope, Earth's 'first true observatory in space'. This programme explains the significance of the observations the telescope will hopefully capture over the next 15 years. Picture: Hubble telescope, Credit: Getty Images